rows.label: qst103912_msg0001
rows.name:
You actually managed to
get a ship! Just what I'd
expect from you, Rex!

rows.label: qst103912_msg0002
rows.name:
As promised, we can now start
the direct, regular route to
Yeshiva Harbor! Great news, eh?

rows.label: qst103912_msg0004
rows.name:
By the way, if I send
90,000G, how much will
Correl-obasan receive now?

rows.label: qst103912_msg0005
rows.name:
The shipping fee from Avaritia to
Yeshiva Harbor has been set at 5%.

rows.label: qst103912_msg0006
rows.name:
It's farther than Gula... and we'll
need a proper escort, so it costs
a bit more than before, but...

rows.label: qst103912_msg0008
rows.name:
Yeshiva Harbor and Iyasaki Village are
right next to each other, so there
shouldn't be any more fees after that.

rows.label: qst103912_msg0009
rows.name:
That's such a huge difference... I'm
glad we made this direct route!

rows.label: qst103912_msg0010
rows.name:
Yeah, and now Correl-obasan
can send her cooking over
more easily than before.

rows.label: qst103912_msg0013
rows.name:
It's freshly made, too!
Looks delicious...!

rows.label: qst103912_msg0014
rows.name:
That's great. ...Right, there's
something I want to ask.

rows.label: qst103912_msg0015
rows.name:
It'd be a big help if you could
assist the guards during
deliveries. What do you say?

rows.label: qst103912_msg0017
rows.name: Thanks, Rex! I'm counting on you!
